WEBVTT

00:02.485 --> 00:06.677
What's the point?

00:07.279 --> 00:08.614
Unless you're one
of the lucky ones

00:08.615 --> 00:10.718
like Maggie from Altadena,

00:10.719 --> 00:12.742
who is spending
this ridiculous day

00:12.743 --> 00:15.527
canoodling with the love
of her life in a snuggie

00:15.559 --> 00:17.174
with three armholes...

00:17.175 --> 00:19.480
And, yes, we actually
live in a world

00:19.481 --> 00:21.419
where that product exists,

00:21.420 --> 00:22.779
I checked online...

00:22.893 --> 00:24.095
But for the rest of us,

00:24.096 --> 00:27.495
the old 2/14 is
just a sad reminder

00:27.496 --> 00:29.558
of everything that's
missing from our lives,

00:29.559 --> 00:31.607
or we never had,

00:31.619 --> 00:33.468
or the one that got away.

00:33.850 --> 00:36.829
So here's to you and
all your near misses

00:36.830 --> 00:39.307
with your little bow
and arrow, Mr. cupid.

00:39.308 --> 00:41.215
Thanks a lot.

00:41.721 --> 00:42.638
This is Nora Walker,

00:42.639 --> 00:45.087
reminding you that mom
is always listening.

00:46.149 --> 00:47.304
Okay, we're out.

00:48.105 --> 00:49.513
What the hell was that?

00:49.619 --> 00:50.094
What?

00:50.095 --> 00:53.518
First you're patronizing some
poor woman and her blanket,

00:53.519 --> 00:55.359
then you start berating a cherub.

00:55.360 --> 00:58.110
Sarah, I was emoting.
That's what I get paid for.

00:58.111 --> 01:01.640
No, mom. You get paid
to be the concerned

01:01.641 --> 01:04.626
but ever-positive mother
that none of us actually have

01:04.694 --> 01:07.105
but that we all need,
especially on holidays.

01:07.106 --> 01:09.133
If this were a real holiday,

01:09.134 --> 01:11.119
the post office would be closed.

01:11.277 --> 01:14.441
Listen, this radio
station is gonna close

01:14.442 --> 01:16.320
if you don't stop this right now.

01:16.321 --> 01:17.992
You know what? Tommy told me

01:17.993 --> 01:19.902
you have been working very
long hours. No, mom...

01:19.903 --> 01:22.395
I really think the overtime
is making you irrational.

01:22.396 --> 01:25.118
Irrational? You're
costing me listeners.

01:25.119 --> 01:27.180
First you break up
with Dr. Karl, who had

01:27.181 --> 01:29.062
our highest-rated show... Karl

01:29.063 --> 01:32.204
leaving the station is
not my responsibility.

01:32.205 --> 01:33.388
That's debatable.

01:33.389 --> 01:34.728
What is your responsibility

01:34.729 --> 01:36.994
is that collective turning off
of radios that just occurred

01:36.995 --> 01:39.326
when you were pining
for him just now.

01:39.327 --> 01:42.379
Oh, come on. I wasn't talking
about Karl, the pill.

01:43.144 --> 01:45.016
Who were you talking about, then?

01:47.540 --> 01:48.994
No one. I...

01:49.057 --> 01:51.154
I was just talking
about life in general,

01:51.155 --> 01:52.548
the old ups and downs.

01:52.549 --> 01:55.702
Well, stop it.
This is not public radio, mom.

01:55.890 --> 01:59.311
Our advertisers like
us warm and fuzzy.

01:59.349 --> 02:02.669
Well, look who's talking.
You're not warm and fuzzy.

02:02.685 --> 02:04.500
You are cold and prickly.

02:04.501 --> 02:07.927
I am not cold and prickly.
I am working, mom.

02:07.928 --> 02:10.466
I could not be happier.
For now, anyway.

02:10.467 --> 02:13.012
Listen to yourself, mom.
You've gone dark.

02:13.374 --> 02:16.305
I need you to get
your mom back, okay?

02:19.140 --> 02:20.973
Warm, fuzzy, love.

02:24.559 --> 02:25.584
Ugh!

02:26.782 --> 02:28.796
Scotty, we're really
booked solid tonight.

02:29.357 --> 02:30.661
You know, in case we
have any walk-ins,

02:30.662 --> 02:33.353
I'm thinking maybe we should
squeeze an extra 2-top

02:33.354 --> 02:34.485
into that corner.

02:35.701 --> 02:37.029
What are you wearing, by the way?

02:37.887 --> 02:40.994
Oh. Uh, Jonathan's coming over.
We're going power walking.

02:40.995 --> 02:42.468
We've been doing
it for a few weeks.

02:42.469 --> 02:44.066
Please tell me you
don't go to the mall.

02:44.067 --> 02:46.221
Is that velour?

02:46.222 --> 02:47.438
Nice.

02:47.611 --> 02:50.207
Make fun of the two old men
who like to walk funny.

02:50.520 --> 02:53.750
See if that gets you into heaven.
I'm sorry. It's... it's cute.

02:54.026 --> 02:56.928
So you guys have been, uh,
seeing a lot of each other, huh?

02:56.929 --> 02:59.033
Don't make it sound like that,
because it's not.

02:59.034 --> 03:01.594
Well, forgive me for being
romantic on Valentine's Day.

03:03.068 --> 03:04.013
Hi.

03:04.857 --> 03:05.487
Jonathan.

03:05.488 --> 03:07.606
Hey. Hey.

03:07.607 --> 03:09.001
You guys match, by the way.

03:09.002 --> 03:10.400
You guys part of a
power walking team?

03:10.401 --> 03:11.655
You're vicious. You know that?

03:12.675 --> 03:13.652
Come on. Let's go.

03:13.736 --> 03:17.323
Wait, wait, wait. Saul,
who's Franklin Norman Beenz?

03:17.324 --> 03:19.725
He made a reservation for
one on Valentine's Day.

03:19.823 --> 03:22.876
Frank N. Beenz? 
You know him?

03:22.877 --> 03:26.174
I know Edward Lemonde.
That's one of his cover names.

03:26.175 --> 03:29.875
You're kidding me. You know
Edward Lemonde, the food critic?

03:29.876 --> 03:32.420
Yeah. W-well, why would he come tonight?
It's a prix fixe.

03:32.421 --> 03:35.266
How well do you know him? Well,
he calls me occasionally.

03:35.376 --> 03:38.576
Really? Well, I accompany
him to restaurants.

03:38.918 --> 03:40.307
Oh, I-I didn't know that.

03:40.308 --> 03:42.339
Well, we're not dating. Whatever.

03:42.689 --> 03:45.303
It'd be fine if you were.
Well, we're not.

03:45.304 --> 03:46.913
Matter of fact,
he called me yesterday.

03:46.914 --> 03:49.618
I told him I was busy.
What... what did he call you about?

03:49.619 --> 03:51.229
Tonight, actually.
He didn't tell me

03:51.230 --> 03:52.521
the name of the restaurant.
Excuse me.

03:52.522 --> 03:54.774
He called you to invite
you to dinner here

03:54.775 --> 03:56.537
for Valentine's Day? 
Yeah.

03:57.200 --> 04:00.224
Hmm. So why did you say no?

04:00.611 --> 04:02.474
Well, I didn't think I'd
be comfortable with it.

04:02.475 --> 04:04.312
But, Jonathan,
he's gonna review us.

04:04.313 --> 04:07.566
What do you want me to do,
try to influence his opinions?

04:07.567 --> 04:09.424
No. Don't look at it that way.

04:09.474 --> 04:12.018
You know, just to
keep him company.

04:12.099 --> 04:12.980
Jonathan, I told you,

04:12.981 --> 04:15.527
I don't mind if you're dating.
We're not dating.

04:15.528 --> 04:19.238
I-I-I-I have an idea.
Why don't you call him back?

04:19.240 --> 04:20.245
I don't think it's too late.

04:20.247 --> 04:22.742
Wait. Laverne,
Shirley has a very bad feeling

04:22.743 --> 04:24.054
about this little scheme of yours.

04:24.055 --> 04:25.739
I don't understand
what the big deal is.

04:25.740 --> 04:27.620
You don't want him
to do this. Come on.

04:27.621 --> 04:30.425
No, no, no. I-I'd
actually love to do it.

04:30.426 --> 04:33.592
As a matter of fact, I should've
said yes in the first place.

04:34.726 --> 04:36.886
I'm power walking,
Saul! I'll be right there!

04:37.115 --> 04:38.551
You realize you're
pimping him out.

04:38.552 --> 04:40.593
Would you be quiet?
He's fine with it.

04:40.665 --> 04:43.721
We don't want a critic eating
alone on Valentine's Day.

04:43.722 --> 04:45.210
I'm coming, Jonathan!

04:45.891 --> 04:46.876
He'll do it.

04:50.659 --> 04:52.194
Okay. I chiffonaded the basil.

04:52.195 --> 04:54.387
All right. I added the
herbes de provence.

04:54.557 --> 04:55.373
Justin, what's next?

04:55.374 --> 04:59.042
Next is, uh, add the...

05:00.119 --> 05:04.646
Ventreche. Uh, yeah, cut that into,
huh, half-inch squares.

05:04.747 --> 05:08.340
All right? Mix in the
dissolved veal demi-glace...

05:08.341 --> 05:10.014
Mm-hmm. While smashing...

05:10.015 --> 05:11.470
While smashing your
head against the wall.

05:11.471 --> 05:13.832
Ser... Could you have picked a
more difficult dinner to make?

05:13.833 --> 05:16.586
Of course it's difficult.
It's cassoulet D'Artagnan...

05:16.809 --> 05:19.993
a French stew with lamb,
duck, veal.

05:20.249 --> 05:22.103
Justin, you don't
promise your fiancÃ©e

05:22.104 --> 05:23.805
a beautiful, romantic,
home-cooked meal,

05:23.806 --> 05:25.618
and then serve up a
plate of spaghetti.

05:25.619 --> 05:27.098
Sarah's been working really hard,
you know? Well...

05:27.099 --> 05:28.404
I want to do something
special for her,

05:28.405 --> 05:29.929
something out of the ordinary.

05:29.930 --> 05:32.581
Well, barnyard soup is
definitely out of the ordinary.

05:32.582 --> 05:34.026
You know what?
You call it what you want,

05:34.027 --> 05:36.399
but it's complex, extravagant.

05:36.400 --> 05:39.811
Women love the big grand gesture.
Yeah, you know, uh, Luc,

05:39.812 --> 05:41.124
I think I'm gonna
disagree with you there.

05:41.125 --> 05:44.300
Uh, I think women like something
a little more personal to them.

05:44.301 --> 05:46.957
Like... like Sarah. You know
what she would like? Chili dogs.

05:47.469 --> 05:50.952
I know, but if I do something
like that for Sarah,

05:51.279 --> 05:54.799
I will look like a cheapstake.
It's, uh, it's cheapskate.

05:54.800 --> 05:56.660
But a cheap steak is
what I'm talking about.

05:56.661 --> 05:59.313
Okay, Dr. Valentine's,
so what are you doing tonight?

05:59.868 --> 06:03.132
Uh... don't have any plans.

06:03.162 --> 06:04.345
Because you don't have a date.

06:04.346 --> 06:05.617
Look, there's a big
game on tonight.

06:05.618 --> 06:07.963
Pizza, Laker girls... It's heaven.

06:07.964 --> 06:10.467
Yeah? Sounds like fun. It is fun.

06:10.468 --> 06:11.619
What's next, Justin?

06:11.620 --> 06:15.715
Next. Next is, uh, okay,
where... Oh. Here it is.

06:15.757 --> 06:18.027
Add that to the thing.

06:18.770 --> 06:19.682
Oh, mon dieu.

06:19.945 --> 06:20.580
Bonjour?

06:20.581 --> 06:23.409
Oh! I was supposed to
soak the beans overnight.

06:23.410 --> 06:25.343
Is that bad? Yeah,
it's bad, Justin.

06:25.344 --> 06:27.199
It's not a cassoulet
without the beans.

06:27.417 --> 06:29.616
If you don't soak the beans overnight,
it's all ruined.

06:33.259 --> 06:35.248
This publishing house
that I'm vetting,

06:35.249 --> 06:38.497
these spreadsheets are...
They're great.

06:38.784 --> 06:39.625
Are you gonna buy it?

06:39.626 --> 06:42.289
I'd like to.
I mean, it's a no-brainer.

06:42.290 --> 06:44.330
Even if we can't turn
this company around,

06:44.331 --> 06:45.862
its physical assets and building

06:45.863 --> 06:47.731
are worth the price itself.

06:48.193 --> 06:50.493
Hey, honey, um, you know,

06:50.494 --> 06:52.598
m-make sure you don't
intimidate Sarah.

06:52.599 --> 06:53.952
You just started working there,

06:53.953 --> 06:56.959
and she needs to know that
she's the one in charge.

06:56.960 --> 06:59.504
I know. I grew up with her.
What are you doing?

06:59.505 --> 07:02.041
Just checking out some
apartments. Oh, good.

07:03.061 --> 07:05.585
Let me see some... Oh, uh, wait. Uh, um...

07:09.797 --> 07:10.526
What is this?

07:10.527 --> 07:13.167
Uh, that's, uh, that's your
mother's high school yearbook.

07:13.546 --> 07:16.009
Honey, I-I thought we agreed
that you were gonna stop...

07:16.010 --> 07:18.378
Did you hear your mom talking
on the radio this morning,

07:18.886 --> 07:21.629
talking about the
one that got away?

07:22.011 --> 07:24.252
That's Brody she was
talking about, Tommy.

07:24.253 --> 07:28.172
Babe, you are going way too far.
She had a framed picture of him.

07:28.173 --> 07:30.916
I saw it. And... and then
she got really uncomfortable

07:30.917 --> 07:32.517
when I asked her about it.

07:32.781 --> 07:33.416
I'm sorry.

07:33.417 --> 07:35.577
Just... the curiosity
is killing me.

07:35.800 --> 07:39.175
Nora, a woman with
eyes for two men...

07:39.277 --> 07:42.701
William Walker and her high
school sweetheart Brody...

07:42.742 --> 07:45.952
when suddenly,
she finds herself pregnant.

07:45.953 --> 07:49.188
Rose. So she elopes with William,

07:49.189 --> 07:51.352
but she has to lie
about the wedding date

07:51.353 --> 07:52.839
because she's knocked up.

07:52.840 --> 07:55.687
And the question still remains...
are you done?

07:55.996 --> 07:56.958
Oh, come on.
Don't you want to know

07:56.959 --> 07:58.848
if Sarah could possibly
be Brody's daughter?

07:58.849 --> 08:00.929
No, I don't.

08:01.302 --> 08:02.710
This is my family.

08:02.870 --> 08:04.591
Sarah is dad's daughter.

08:04.859 --> 08:08.155
Please don't mention
this to anybody.

08:08.272 --> 08:09.589
Promise me, all right?

08:09.631 --> 08:12.499
Things are going good.
I don't want to screw it up.

08:13.104 --> 08:14.592
Okay, I promise.

08:15.221 --> 08:16.534
Okay? No.

08:18.031 --> 08:19.247
Consider it over.

08:21.008 --> 08:21.935
Okay.

08:22.777 --> 08:24.924
Mwah. I'll see you tonight, okay?

08:24.925 --> 08:25.822
Okay.

08:25.823 --> 08:26.768
Love ya.

08:28.493 --> 08:29.870
Happy Valentine's Day.

