D.N.A. in this family?

26:11.381 --> 26:12.898
Trust me. Don't do it.

26:12.899 --> 26:14.473
The kid's right.
Can we please leave?

26:14.474 --> 26:15.806
No, Kevin.

26:15.807 --> 26:19.112
I'm not gonna let you all
jump on the mom bandwagon

26:19.113 --> 26:21.464
and push this thing under the rug.

26:21.465 --> 26:24.949
Dad did not sign my
birth certificate.

26:24.950 --> 26:26.863
So what, now he's not your father?

26:26.864 --> 26:28.278
He could've been away on business.

26:28.279 --> 26:29.321
Sarah, it's the '60s.

26:29.322 --> 26:30.581
He could've been passed
out in the waiting room

26:30.582 --> 26:32.126
with a cigar hanging
out of his mouth.

26:32.127 --> 26:33.950
Guys, look, obviously,
she's not gonna stop.

26:33.951 --> 26:35.790
Can we all agree,
she should just speak to mom?

26:35.791 --> 26:37.993
I get it, Tommy.
You want me to believe mom

26:37.994 --> 26:39.506
so that she'll let
rose off the hook

26:39.507 --> 26:40.898
for the bringing
this whole thing up.

26:40.899 --> 26:41.975
Oh, and you'd hate that.

26:41.976 --> 26:44.098
Oh, shut up, Tommy.
I am so done with you today.

26:44.099 --> 26:45.320
Well, what are you gonna do,
fire me?

26:45.321 --> 26:46.725
Guys. We're not at work.

26:46.726 --> 26:48.263
Sarah, you're overreacting.

26:48.264 --> 26:49.574
I'm done with you, too, Kevin.

26:49.575 --> 26:50.824
Great. Can I leave now? No!

26:50.825 --> 26:53.962
Let the poor guy go, man.
He's got airport head.

26:54.369 --> 26:57.244
Look, Sarah, we all agree.
It's nothing.

26:57.245 --> 26:59.303
No, no, no, no.
It's not nothing, Tommy.

26:59.304 --> 27:01.045
It is something,
and how about a little bit of,

27:01.046 --> 27:04.584
"yeah, Sarah's freaking out,
and she has every right to be,

27:04.585 --> 27:07.252
and we are all there
supporting her"?

27:08.025 --> 27:09.494
God, I-if Kitty was here,

27:09.495 --> 27:11.528
at least I would have
someone on my side.

27:11.529 --> 27:13.298
Yeah, her and her other dad.

27:14.478 --> 27:15.807
Oh, I'm kidding.

27:16.062 --> 27:17.182
Where are you going?

27:17.183 --> 27:18.202
What does it matter, Tommy?

27:18.203 --> 27:19.511
Obviously,
this is not your concern.

27:19.512 --> 27:21.099
It's none of your concern.

27:31.216 --> 27:33.986
We should go back to that
bistro in Santa Barbara.

27:33.987 --> 27:35.863
Yes. Remember?

27:36.237 --> 27:38.026
Just you and me,

27:38.048 --> 27:39.834
balmy nights,

27:39.835 --> 27:42.200
the moon on the water.

27:42.201 --> 27:44.447
Speaking of water,
I could use some.

27:44.766 --> 27:46.932
Waiter. May I have
some water, please?

27:48.738 --> 27:50.744
Are you all right,
Jonathan? You look a bit flushed.

27:50.745 --> 27:52.846
No, I'm... I'm...
I'm fine. I'm fine.

27:52.847 --> 27:56.264
What did you say our entrÃ©e was?
It was so delicious.

27:56.265 --> 27:58.174
