27:58.175 --> 27:59.791
It was a fillet of sole bercy

27:59.792 --> 28:02.093
with, uh, chanterelle
mushrooms and, uh...

28:02.094 --> 28:04.601
Mm. But what was in the sauce? The sauce?

28:04.602 --> 28:05.999
Yes.

28:06.000 --> 28:07.748
Fish. Oh.

28:07.749 --> 28:10.566
I believe I detected shrimp.

28:10.567 --> 28:11.449
Shrimp?

28:11.450 --> 28:14.470
Oh. I know my shrimp when
I taste it. Am I right?

28:15.890 --> 28:18.872
Well, the... the...
the... the veloutÃ©...

28:18.873 --> 28:24.347
The veloutÃ© was of a...
shrimpish nature.

28:24.348 --> 28:25.153
Oh.

28:25.154 --> 28:27.373
Do you have a problem with shrimp?

28:28.809 --> 28:31.185
No, no, no.

28:31.186 --> 28:33.548
I love shrimp.

28:33.549 --> 28:36.758
Oh, the sauce was so delicious,

28:36.759 --> 28:39.779
I practically licked my plate.

28:39.780 --> 28:41.239
Ah...

28:42.062 --> 28:46.497
Funny. I never noticed how...
sexy your voice is.

28:46.498 --> 28:49.007
Well, I-I will certainly pay
your compliments to the chef.

28:49.008 --> 28:50.733
Please do.

28:52.196 --> 28:54.103
Table nine. Got it.

28:54.104 --> 28:58.215
It's 2 for table 14.

28:58.574 --> 29:00.777
Hey, how's it going?
Is everything all right?

29:00.778 --> 29:02.256
Oh, yes. I just have
to get their desserts.

29:02.257 --> 29:03.381
Everything is gonna be fine.

29:03.382 --> 29:06.382
It's gonna be fine? Why? What...
what's going on?

29:06.383 --> 29:09.608
Jonathan is just feeling a
little warm. That's all.

29:09.744 --> 29:11.446
Warm? He looks like he's sweating.

29:11.447 --> 29:14.934
Ah, yes. This is gonna fix it.
This'll be great.

29:15.375 --> 29:18.356
You did tell him there was
shrimp in the veloutÃ©, right?

29:18.901 --> 29:20.448
Saul.

29:20.991 --> 29:22.088
Not in so many words.

29:22.089 --> 29:23.481
In any words?

29:23.482 --> 29:24.456
No.

29:24.457 --> 29:26.656
Oh, my God. Well,
it's not such a big deal.

29:26.657 --> 29:28.113
He just said he
felt a little warm.

29:28.114 --> 29:30.720
His throat is constricting,
but on the plus side...

29:30.721 --> 29:32.654
They loved the sole.

29:32.655 --> 29:34.196
This is a nightmare.

29:34.197 --> 29:35.987
He's gonna be fine.
Wait till you see.

29:35.988 --> 29:38.453
The sugar in the cake is
gonna counteract the shrimp.

29:38.454 --> 29:39.935
Oh, is that true?

29:39.936 --> 29:40.946
I don't know.

29:40.947 --> 29:41.885
What were you thinking?

29:41.886 --> 29:43.974
I wasn't thinking.

29:43.975 --> 29:45.602
They're out there having
fun at my expense.

29:45.603 --> 29:47.020
Do you know they're planning
on going on vacation?

29:47.021 --> 29:48.864
I don't care. This was
about a good review.

29:48.865 --> 29:50.386
You're both acting like teenagers.

29:50.387 --> 29:51.657
He started it!

29:51.658 --> 29:53.741
And you're gonna end it by putting
him into anaphylactic shock?

29:53.742 --> 29:55.143
I'm not gonna put him
into any kind of shock.

29:55.144 --> 29:57.309
If he goes into shock, there's
an epipen in the first aid kit,

29:57.310 --> 29:59.588
and I will apply it.
You need to calm down.

29:59.589 --> 30:01.642
He's probably out there talking
about the food right now.

30:01.575 --> 30:03.276
Talking? Sure,
if he can still talk.

30:03.277 --> 30:05.547
He's fine. They're fine.

30:07.561 --> 30:10.277
They're gone. Thanks a lot.

30:12.452 --> 30:13.746
Sarah, please.

30:13.747 --> 30:15.722
Would you just sit down? No.

30:17.175 --> 30:18.951
Honey, listen.

30:18.952 --> 30:20.670
Understand, back in those days,

30:20.671 --> 30:22.776
if you got pregnant and
you weren't married,

30:22.777 --> 30:25.197
it was a very big deal.
I mean, the neighbors

30:25.198 --> 30:27.230
would hold a press
conference for God sakes.

30:27.231 --> 30:29.796
Mom, I'm not here to
discuss your wedding date.

30:29.797 --> 30:32.015
All right, yes. I-I lied to you.

30:32.016 --> 30:34.003
I lied to you because I wanted you

30:34.004 --> 30:36.303
to never have a
doubt in your mind.

30:36.304 --> 30:38.239
Your father and I
loved each other...

30:38.240 --> 30:41.126
Did you sleep with
this Brody guy or not?

30:43.611 --> 30:45.195
Yes. Once.

30:48.554 --> 30:49.729
When?

30:50.560 --> 30:52.946
I don't remember. Mom,
was it around the time that I was...

30:52.947 --> 30:55.890
Yes. Oh, my God.
This is... this is not happening.

30:55.891 --> 30:57.325
This is who you were
talking about on the radio

30:57.326 --> 30:59.801
this morning, wasn't it,
the one that got away?

31:00.332 --> 31:02.271
That was Brody. You think he...

31:02.272 --> 31:04.138
You think he might be my... No.

31:04.139 --> 31:06.738
Sarah, no.

31:07.767 --> 31:10.354
Listen to me.
The only reason your father

31:10.355 --> 31:12.676
didn't sign your birth
certificate that night

31:12.677 --> 31:15.923
was because he was worried that
maybe you weren't his daughter.

31:15.924 --> 31:17.495
And what made him change his mind?

31:17.496 --> 31:19.622
Because they had a blood test.

31:20.618 --> 31:24.328
They both took a
blood test, Sarah.

31:25.048 --> 31:27.140
Brody was o negative,

31:27.141 --> 31:28.717
which ruled him out
since you're...

31:28.718 --> 31:31.159
AB. AB, yes.

31:35.039 --> 31:37.011
And what color are his eyes?

31:37.012 --> 31:39.188
My God. You don't believe me.

31:39.189 --> 31:41.390
I don't know, mom. I know
that you're capable of lying

31:41.391 --> 31:42.572
to protect the people you love.

31:42.573 --> 31:45.884
What color are his eyes?
I don't remember.

31:45.885 --> 31:47.677
Why don't you go find
out for yourself?

31:47.678 --> 31:49.928
No, better yet, why don't
you go have a d.N.A. Test?

31:49.929 --> 31:51.451
Then you can find
out all the facts.

31:51.452 --> 31:53.449
And when you know them
and you know the truth,

31:53.450 --> 31:56.087
you come back here and
you apologize to me,

31:56.088 --> 31:57.999
because I'll deserve it.

32:16.564 --> 32:18.203
Do you believe her?

32:18.557 --> 32:20.175
I have no reason not to.

32:20.800 --> 32:23.052
But I understand,
it's not simple for you.

32:23.781 --> 32:26.163
If you want to find this
man and talk to him,

32:26.617 --> 32:28.215
that's what you should do.

32:28.603 --> 32:29.656
Mm.

32:30.388 --> 32:31.304
God. Thank you.

32:31.305 --> 32:33.002
I feel like you're
the first person

32:33.003 --> 32:34.905
to listen to me all day.

32:35.292 --> 32:37.401
I'd love to listen to
you and I will help you

32:38.368 --> 32:39.935
if you let me in.

32:40.931 --> 32:42.604
What are you talking about?

32:42.794 --> 32:44.630
You know how nuts I was today,

32:44.911 --> 32:46.773
trying to plan this amazing night?

32:48.327 --> 32:48.938
I don't understand

32:48.939 --> 32:50.900
why you didn't tell
me what was going on.

32:50.901 --> 32:53.312
Well, you left the bowling
alley before I had a chance to.

32:53.313 --> 32:56.186
No, Sarah, before,
when you first heard.

32:56.187 --> 32:58.803
You told me it was work. Come on.
It was pretty hard to explain.

32:58.804 --> 33:01.490
My head was spinning.
How could I help you

33:01.491 --> 33:04.328
if I don't know a single
thing you do all day long?

33:05.286 --> 33:06.950
You mean like work stuff?

33:06.951 --> 33:10.159
Mm-hmm. I'm your partner.

33:10.160 --> 33:11.783
I don't want you to shut me out.

33:12.539 --> 33:14.281
You really feel I shut you out?

33:14.282 --> 33:17.371
Yeah. That's why I was trying
to plan this amazing evening.

33:18.203 --> 33:20.050
I need to find a way back in.

33:22.357 --> 33:25.150
Luc, I-I'm really sorry.
I had no idea.

33:25.930 --> 33:28.012
I don't want to shut you out.

33:28.013 --> 33:29.494
I want to share.

33:30.530 --> 33:34.976
Okay, I will talk about
the most boring, tedious,

33:35.358 --> 33:38.802
dull work stuff that
I can possibly find.

33:38.803 --> 33:40.382
In fact, I would like to do that,

33:40.383 --> 33:42.285
because right now,
it would be a great distraction

33:42.286 --> 33:44.420
for the day I just had.

33:47.361 --> 33:48.891
It's gonna be okay.

33:49.409 --> 33:50.555
Thank you.

33:55.392 --> 33:58.180
I want to believe mom.
I really do.

34:12.844 --> 34:14.788
I thought maybe you were Sarah.

34:16.464 --> 34:17.539
Sorry.

34:18.725 --> 34:21.193
I'm sure I'm the last person
you want to see right now.

34:21.300 --> 34:22.399
One of 'em.

34:23.803 --> 34:25.965
It's this damn family tree.

34:26.902 --> 34:27.900
It's done.

34:27.902 --> 34:30.659
There it is. You can
burn it for all I care.

34:31.150 --> 34:33.021
Just try to understand

34:33.022 --> 34:35.589
that I never wanted to
cause all this strife.

34:35.978 --> 34:38.228
What did you want?

34:38.561 --> 34:40.348
No good would ever come of it.

34:40.349 --> 34:43.321
Can you imagine what would've
happened had this been true?

34:43.871 --> 34:47.362
I'm sorry. You had no right
to dig into my family's past

34:47.362 --> 34:49.687
to satisfy your own curiosity.

34:50.034 --> 34:52.681
Here. Thanks.

34:52.681 --> 34:55.246
And let me tell you,
you can't bring this family down.

34:55.248 --> 34:57.251
We've been through a lot worse,
and we're still here.

34:57.252 --> 34:59.977
We're screaming at each other,
but we're still here.

35:01.833 --> 35:03.479
I feel terrible.

35:04.076 --> 35:05.474
Well, good.

35:08.995 --> 35:10.720
I don't know what to do.

35:10.934 --> 35:12.602
Why don't you do what we all do?

35:12.826 --> 35:15.230
Have a glass of wine and
wait for the dust to settle.

35:15.231 --> 35:16.820
And if you're gonna be
part of this family,

35:16.821 --> 35:19.103
you need to learn to get over it.

35:19.104 --> 35:20.900
Stop crying.

35:22.759 --> 35:23.884
Okay.

35:26.050 --> 35:27.006
So...

35:28.306 --> 35:30.307
It all comes down
to this question...

35:32.350 --> 35:33.816
Red or white?

35:35.366 --> 35:36.513
Red.

35:48.662 --> 35:49.865
Jonathan.

35:50.707 --> 35:51.818
Is Scotty here?

35:51.819 --> 35:54.207
No. Yeah, he's upstairs.

35:54.208 --> 35:55.634
Kevin came back.
He wasn't supposed to...

35:55.635 --> 35:57.605
Yes or no is all I need.

35:59.155 --> 36:00.491
Yeah, yeah,

36:00.951 --> 36:02.162
he's here.

36:02.266 --> 36:04.783
Tell him it's my fault
that we left so abruptly.

36:05.950 --> 36:08.131
I had to get out or
stay and make a scene.

36:08.132 --> 36:10.355
Are you okay? Yeah, I'm fine.

36:10.356 --> 36:12.961
Nothing a little
antihistamine wouldn't fix.

36:13.325 --> 36:16.326
That's not the scene
I'm talking about.

36:17.202 --> 36:19.822
Tell Scotty that Edward's
coming back another night.

36:19.823 --> 36:21.832
Great, great.

36:21.924 --> 36:25.551
I, for one, will, uh,
not be returning anytime soon.

36:25.552 --> 36:29.138
Jonathan, wait. Wait.
Please. Come on. Please.

36:29.383 --> 36:32.152
It was so stupid and
childish and thoughtless,

36:32.153 --> 36:33.100
this whole thing.

36:33.101 --> 36:37.039
I-I-I-I think that I
literally lost my mind.

36:37.040 --> 36:39.650
Why? That's all I want to know.

36:39.651 --> 36:41.636
Just listen to me, okay?

36:44.572 --> 36:47.801
You make me feel insecure.
Can you understand that?

36:48.481 --> 36:49.928
I make you feel insecure?

36:49.929 --> 36:50.638
Yeah.

36:50.707 --> 36:53.289
I wasted almost 20
years of my life drunk.

36:53.290 --> 36:54.438
Jonathan, listen to me.

36:54.439 --> 36:56.817
You make me feel insecure.
I can't help it.

36:57.454 --> 36:59.096
That's the way it is,
and then tonight,

36:59.097 --> 37:01.461
I see you with that
loathsome man...

37:01.462 --> 37:03.134
I told you,
he doesn't interest me.

37:03.135 --> 37:04.663
But I didn't believe you.

37:06.072 --> 37:08.405
And suddenly it feels like
it's the '80s again...

37:08.406 --> 37:10.023
All those people who lined up

37:10.024 --> 37:12.288
waiting to spend some
time with you, remember?

37:12.469 --> 37:15.432
You know, somehow
I actually thought

37:15.758 --> 37:19.278
we had put our past behind us.

37:19.279 --> 37:20.940
I'm trying. You're trying.

37:20.941 --> 37:23.365
We're both trying to
understand our lives.

37:23.366 --> 37:25.776
If we could live them over again,
maybe we would...

37:25.777 --> 37:28.486
Try to make them differently, yes.

37:28.487 --> 37:29.511
Maybe.

37:34.090 --> 37:35.696
I behaved like a...

37:36.374 --> 37:38.352
Like an ass tonight, too.

37:39.160 --> 37:41.762
God, we could've been in
high school tonight, right?

37:43.873 --> 37:44.839
Oh.

37:45.700 --> 37:49.255
Probably explains why
this man that I slept with

37:49.256 --> 37:50.215
all those years ago

37:50.216 --> 37:52.772
who doesn't even remember
that it happened,

37:53.091 --> 37:55.050
who probably gave me h.I.V.,

37:55.659 --> 37:58.870
is the only man that
I'm interested in now.

37:59.956 --> 38:01.049
Well...

38:02.495 --> 38:05.002
Hard as it is for
you to believe...

38:06.235 --> 38:09.488
You're the one I'm most
interested in, too.

38:09.897 --> 38:12.496
Oh, God. Well,
why didn't you say something?

38:12.497 --> 38:13.876
I'm sorry,

38:14.130 --> 38:18.069
but... we all are afraid

38:18.070 --> 38:20.099
of taking the first step.

38:20.450 --> 38:21.699
Yeah.

38:22.224 --> 38:24.027
Which probably explains

38:25.571 --> 38:27.918
why I've never done this before.

38:44.718 --> 38:46.847
Wait. Where are you...
Where are you going?

38:46.848 --> 38:49.791
I'm power walking to my car,
and then I'm driving home.

38:51.578 --> 38:52.991
Care to join me?

38:53.478 --> 38:54.873
Oh, yeah.

39:12.402 --> 39:15.643
Hey. Where, uh, where's mom?

39:15.644 --> 39:16.688
Upstairs.

39:16.689 --> 39:18.526
She finally called it a day.

39:18.527 --> 39:21.337
Not before we put
away a bottle of wine

39:21.338 --> 39:23.630
and taught me to bake
your favorite cookies.

39:23.752 --> 39:25.413
B-but what'd you say to her?

39:25.414 --> 39:28.558
Not much. She did
most of the talking.

39:28.559 --> 39:29.526
Yeah.

39:30.029 --> 39:31.701
She's quite a woman, huh?

39:33.062 --> 39:35.595
Did... did she say
anything about Brody?

39:35.871 --> 39:36.784
We were wrong.

39:36.785 --> 39:38.190
Yeah, I know.

39:40.191 --> 39:42.127
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

39:45.110 --> 39:46.334
Here.

39:48.596 --> 39:51.421
Your mom said that you
used to lick the frosting

39:51.422 --> 39:53.192
and then eat the cookie.

39:53.425 --> 39:55.825
Yeah. When I was 10.

39:55.826 --> 39:56.778
Oh.

39:57.496 --> 40:00.389
Well... happy Valentine's Day.

40:01.133 --> 40:02.799
You, too.

40:14.525 --> 40:16.299
Scotty, this is delicious.

40:16.300 --> 40:18.955
I am so glad you came home.

40:19.179 --> 40:21.649
I wasn't gonna miss
Valentine's with you.

40:21.650 --> 40:23.175
I love you. Mwah.

40:23.176 --> 40:24.554
I love you.

40:29.262 --> 40:30.531
What's wrong?

40:31.912 --> 40:34.861
Is this the entre with the shrimp?
Oh, screw you.

40:34.862 --> 40:36.615
I think I'm dying. Fine. Go ahead.

40:36.616 --> 40:39.844
I want you to have my
Olivia Newton-John...

40:40.052 --> 40:41.745
Action figure.

40:44.354 --> 40:45.104
I'm sorry.

40:45.105 --> 40:48.492
I was just trying to...
lighten things up about Saul.

40:50.838 --> 40:52.519
You know, people make mistakes,

40:52.520 --> 40:54.087
especially when it comes to love.

40:54.278 --> 40:56.006
Oh, come on. Do you
really think he's in love?

40:56.007 --> 40:58.610
Yeah, in his own peculiar way.

41:00.518 --> 41:02.338
You should forgive him, Scotty.

41:03.831 --> 41:06.329
Well, people have forgiven
me in the past, so...

41:10.462 --> 41:12.074
I'm glad I came home.

41:12.717 --> 41:13.940
Me, too.

41:17.624 --> 41:19.433
Happy Valentine's Day.

41:20.904 --> 41:22.551
Happy Valentine's Day.

41:26.072 --> 41:28.919
Yesterday, I, Nora Walker,

41:28.920 --> 41:31.011
your own dear mom,

41:31.012 --> 41:34.613
found herself
slandering a holiday.

41:34.805 --> 41:37.121
Yes, it was not my finest moment.

41:37.122 --> 41:38.342
But the good news is,

41:38.343 --> 41:41.159
